verbose_text: The expression levels of inflammatory cytokines TNF-alpha, IFN-gamma, and IL-8 in serum significantly increased in the model group (p < 0.01 for all); compared with levels in the model group, the expression levels of inflammatory cytokines TNF-alpha, IFN-gamma, and IL-8 significantly decreased in the hydrogen treatment group (p < 0.01 for TNF-alpha and IFN-gamma; p < 0.05 for IL-8) (XREF_FIG.
